 and concluded that, at least when modelling large, nearby\ngalaxies, 1D techniques have more advantages than 2D techniques. Finally, we\ndeveloped a prescription to estimate the uncertainties on the 1D best-fit\nparameters for the 66 spheroids that takes into account systematic errors,\nunlike popular 2D codes that only consider statistical errors.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 23 Nov 2015 21:00:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 15 Mar 2016 23:31:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-17"}
